$interpreted: Noble Lady: So you're the rumored child who was found and taken in by King Theodore?
Alice: U, uncle king is very kind to me...
Noble Lady: Did you not cry from how scary his Majesty looks? Not even once?

Alice: Umm, uncle king is not scary.
I know another girl who is much scarier...
Noble Gentleman: Hmmm~ she is indeed cute, but then again, every little child is cute~
Noble Gentleman: I don't get it. What did his Majesty see in you that makes you so special to him?
Ralph: His Majesty wants to see you.
Alice: Eh? Why?
Ralph: His Majesty wants to ask you if you know the method to chop down the tree safely.
Ralph: ... Listen carefully. The person his Majesty sees is not you.
Alice: Who are you talking about?
Ralph: You reminded him of his niece when she was still a little girl.
Ralph: That's the reason he didn't lock you up. All he did was assign me to keep a close eye on you.
Ralph: He has no special feelings for you. So don't be full of yourse——
Theodore: When has it become your business to interpret my intentions, Ralph?
Ralph: Your Majesty, you're here...
Theodore: So, did you hear from her about how to chop down the tree?
Alice: I heard it from Ralph. Uncle king, you're chopping down the tree!?
Theodore: Yes. The number of monsters attracted to that tree is getting out of hand.

Theodore: In addition, the mysterious tri-colored crystals around the tree are continuing to proliferate. 
If we don't deal with it right away, 
it could harm the capital and army camps around it.

Alice: B, but, Deemo is still in that tree!
Before we chop down the tree, we need to save Deemo first...
Theodore: Deemo?

Ralph: Your Majesty, that is the name of this little girl's companion. Currently, he seems to be trapped atop that monstrous tree. 
We do not know whether he's alive or not.

Alice: Deemo is definitely still alive and well!
I believe in Deemo!
Theodore: So what? You want me to ignore the safety of my people and the soldiers just so you can save your companion?

General: Y, Your Majesty, she is still a child.
You might frighten her if you keep raising your voice...
Theodore: Shut it! I'm talking to her!

Alice: That's not it...
... I just... don't want to... sacrifice anybody...
Theodore: Do not speak such naive words!
Theodore: Sacrificing a few for the greater good; that is the obvious and correct choice! Why can't any of you understand this!?
Alice: ... Any?
Ralph: Your Majesty——
Theodore: Regardless of who it is, if the situation calls for it, one must have the will to cut all personal ties!
Theodore: Only the weak will hesitate. Without the proper resolve, you people will only make things worse in this cruel and unforgiving world!
Ralph: Your Majesty Theodore! Please cease your anger!
Theodore: I thought she was...
Theodore: ......
Theodore: Ralph, what are you staring at? Help her up!
Alice: ... To be honest, I don't really understand what you just said.
Theodore: ......
Alice: What I do understand is that when I fell into the treehouse, I was all alone too. I couldn't do anything...
Alice: However, Deemo was still kind to me and he still cared about me.
Theodore: Enough! Stop talking!

Alice: When I was sad, Deemo would play the piano for me.
He didn't choose to sacrifice me.
Theodore: You...
Alice: ... Therefore, if your world doesn't want Deemo to exist, then it is definitely wrong! I don't want to be in your world either!
Theodore: ......
Theodore: Whatever you desire. Ralph, take her to the root of the monstrous tree.
Ralph: It has become a gathering place for monsters. It's quite dangerous. Besides, it is not the appropriate time for me to leave your Majesty's side...
Theodore: I said take her there. You do as I say.
Ralph: ... Yes, your Majesty.
Theodore: Since you decided to leave, don't you ever dare to return to my side.
Alice: ......
Ralph: ... We're here.
Alice: ... Yes...
Ralph: Well then, I have indeed completed his Majesty Theodore's order.
Alice: ... Ralph?

Ralph: This is the most critical moment for his Majesty right now. Everything is depending on this war. 
I will not allow you to disrupt his thoughts.
Ralph: For the sake of his Majesty Theodore──
Ralph: ──Die!
Alice: The sound of the piano... Deemo!?

Alice: This place... It looks a bit like the treehouse, yet it feels a bit different...
It's bizarre... yet beautiful at the same time...
Alice: The sound of the piano! Right, I have to find Deemo!
Alice: Follow the piano music...
Alice: Deemo!
Alice: Ah! Are those... notes!?
Alice: One note... two notes... four notes...
Alice: I get it! Deemo! I will rescue you right away!

Alice: Ugh, without the gold melody... it's not complete...
I was so close to Deemo already...
Alice: Darn it. These branches...!

Alice: ... You want me to run away by myself?
I will never do such a terrible thing to Deemo!
Alice: ... Wait a second. Deemo, what are you going to do!?

Alice: No! If you do that, it's even less likely that the tree will let you go!
Deemo, don't leave me alone!
